cartesian length optimization; cythonization

adds header file for vectorgeo, allowing types to be imported elsewhere
(may make sense to move these into a new file)

in the following benchmark, length property computes 700+ times faster

    import karta
    import numpy as np
    import time

    xy = np.random.rand(100000, 2)
    line = karta.Line(xy, crs=karta.crs.CartesianCRS)

    t0 = time.time()
    d = line.length
    t = time.time()-t0
    print(t)
    print(d)

    t0 = time.time()
    d_old = line.length_old
    t_old = time.time()-t0
    print(t_old)
    print(d_old)

    print("speed-up: {0:.1f}x".format(t_old/t))

Fix sockjs not working behind haproxy

For some reason the websocket connection runs into a timeout, the xhr
transport doesn't properly take over, and then stuff takes ages to
realign again.

Only happens under Tornado 5, doesn't happen under Tornado 4.5

Increasing the timeout for now instead of pinning to Tornado 4.5 in the
hopes that might still be figured out.

Incredibly weird though.

Better solution for the Tornado 5 + SockJS + haproxy issue

Looks like Nagle's algorithm was the cause. Adding

    option http-no-delay

to haproxy.cfg solves the problem without modification of the timeout,
however that is not an option for the thousands of instances already
deployed in the field.

So instead we add 300ms to the roundtrip based connection timeout, that
should hopefully get around any Nagle-induced delays (usually between
40 and 200ms according to various sites on the net).

Add NineOldAndroids library.

When running animations that do not involve concatenated, multiplied or inverted
2D matrices, use NineOldAndroids to gain the benefits of Honeycomb+ animations.

If an animation's transform property is non-null and set to a Ti2DMatrix which
is the result of matrix.multiply or matrix.invert, or if the matrix contains
concatenations of the *same* operation such as...

    transform: Ti.UI.create2DMatrix().rotate(45).rotate(45),

... then revert to using old animation system. Concatenations of
*different* operations, such as...

    transform: Ti.UI.create2DMatrix().rotate(45).scale(2,2),

... will, however, be done with the newer animation system since
they can easily be translated into multiple property animators.
